nib.text:
A woman was injured in a shooting Monday afternoon in North Minneapolis, police said.

Minneapolis police officers responded to a report of a person shot near the Marathon Gas Station on the 1100 block of West Broadway Avenue around 1:35 p.m.

When they arrived, officers found a woman who was shot once. 

According to a spokesman for the Minneapolis Police Department, the woman was taken to a local hospital for treatment of the injury which was considered not life-threatening.

The suspect fled the area in a vehicle before police arrived.

The circumstances surrounding the shooting remain under investigation.
